    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Governor
                            <persName type="to">McIntire</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your letter of the 15th instant, stating the opinions of the attorney-general of
                    Colorado and of the district judge in regard to the Walsenburg lynching, that a
                    grand jury drawn from any other county than Huerfano would not have
                    jurisdiction.</p>
                <p>I have transmitted copies of your letter and its inclosure to the Italian
                    ambassador.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
